content.text:
The syntax of the `switch` statement is:
```javascript
switch (expression) {
  case value1:
    // code to execute if expression equals value1
    break;
  case value2:
    // code to execute if expression equals value2
    break;
  default:
    // code to execute if no cases match
}
```
- **Expression**: The value to compare (e.g., a variable).
- **case**: Defines a specific value to compare against the expression.
- **break**: Exits the `switch` statement after executing the matching `case`.
- **default**: Executes if no `case` matches (optional).

content.code:
// Basic switch example
const day = 'Wednesday';
switch (day) {
  case 'Monday':
    console.log('The week starts!');
    break;
  case 'Wednesday':
    console.log('Midweek!');
    break;
  case 'Friday':
    console.log('Almost weekend!');
    break;
  default:
    console.log('Another day.');
}
// Output: Midweek!

// Example without break
const fruit = 'Apple';
switch (fruit) {
  case 'Apple':
    console.log('This is an apple.');
  case 'Pear':
    console.log('This is a pear.');
  default:
    console.log('Another fruit.');
}
// Output:
// This is an apple.
// This is a pear.
// Another fruit.

// Correct example with break
switch (fruit) {
  case 'Apple':
    console.log('This is an apple.');
    break;
  case 'Pear':
    console.log('This is a pear.');
    break;
  default:
    console.log('Another fruit.');
}
// Output: This is an apple.

// Example with default
const grade = 'B';
switch (grade) {
  case 'A':
    console.log('Excellent result!');
    break;
  case 'B':
    console.log('Good result!');
    break;
  case 'C':
    console.log('Satisfactory result.');
    break;
  default:
    console.log('No grade entered.');
}
// Output: Good result!

// Multiple case example
const day = 'Saturday';
switch (day) {
  case 'Saturday':
  case 'Sunday':
    console.log('It’s a weekend!');
    break;
  case 'Monday':
  case 'Wednesday':
  case 'Friday':
    console.log('It’s a weekday.');
    break;
  default:
    console.log('Unknown day.');
}
// Output: It’s a weekend!

// Error-prone example
// Error: Missing break
const number = 2;
switch (number) {
  case 1:
    console.log('One');
  case 2:
    console.log('Two');
  case 3:
    console.log('Three');
  default:
    console.log('Another number');
}
// Output:
// Two
// Three
// Another number

// Correct approach
switch (number) {
  case 1:
    console.log('One');
    break;
  case 2:
    console.log('Two');
    break;
  case 3:
    console.log('Three');
    break;
  default:
    console.log('Another number');
}
// Output: Two

// switch example
const month = 'January';
switch (month) {
  case 'January':
    console.log('Winter month');
    break;
  case 'July':
    console.log('Summer month');
    break;
  default:
    console.log('Another month');
}
// Output: Winter month

// Same example with if-else
if (month === 'January') {
  console.log('Winter month');
} else if (month === 'July') {
  console.log('Summer month');
} else {
  console.log('Another month');
}
// Output: Winter month

